column8: Water line starting to develop some tenacious algae, indicative of failing paint in this area

While paint coverage remains good, antifouling properties are failing allowing heavily embedded black algae through. Many areas will retain a “dirty” appearance until after next haulout, though all protruding growth will continue to be removed.
About a dozen blisters observed on starboard side, from nickel to silver dollar sized.
Prop nut anode due for replacement on next service.
